{"word":"ἀγύμναστος","slug":"ἀγύμναστος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀγύμναστος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:γυμνάζω'><el>γυμνάζω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>unexercised, untrained</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>unpractised</i>, <el>τινός</el> in a thing, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; also <el>εἴς, πρός</el> or <el>περί τι</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>unharassed</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <el>ἀγυμνάστως ἔχειν πρός τι</el> <i>to be unpractised</i> in a thing, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}